&lt;p&gt;QphoX is looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Head of Product&lt;/strong&gt; to lead the transformation of our quantum transducer technologies from R&amp;amp;D prototypes to scalable, market-ready products. As Head of Product, you will define and execute the product strategy, align the roadmap with QphoX’s strategic objectives, and work closely with the engineering, fabrication, and business teams to deliver our next-generation offerings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a member of our team, you will help develop and produce the next generation of integrated transducers and take their performance to the next level. You will bridge technical excellence and commercial impact, ensuring our products meet customer needs and quality standards at every stage of development while working with the most advanced techniques and state-of-the-art tools available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be involved in:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, mentor and manage a cross-functional engineering team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain the product roadmap, ensuring alignment with QphoX’s long-term vision and commercial strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the process of taking technologies from R&amp;amp;D through validation, scaling, and market introduction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interface with external partners, suppliers and customers to gather feedback, define product requirements, and validate solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify market trends, customer needs and emerging opportunities in the quantum hardware ecosystem.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish systems for documentation, product lifecycle management, and cross-departmental coordination.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with nanofabrication, quantum engineering, and business development teams to translate technical progress into product value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills and knowledge you will bring to QphoX:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MSc or PhD in Physics, Engineering, Materials Science, or a related technical discipline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years’ experience in product management or technical leadership, ideally in deep-tech, semiconductor, photonics, or quantum hardware.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of R&amp;amp;D to production transitions in high-tech or nanofabrication environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to manage interdisciplinary teams and coordinate across engineering, fabrication and business functions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organizational and communication skills, with a collaborative and inclusive leadership style.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic thinker with a hands-on approach and able to translate complex technology into actionable roadmaps and deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Ideal Candidate:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are a technically fluent, strategically minded leader who thrives in bridging science and business. You enjoy working in fast-paced, multidisciplinary environments, where collaboration, curiosity, and clear communication are key. You combine a detail-oriented mindset with a passion for building the infrastructure that will enable the quantum future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Teamwork is an essential value of our company, hence fitting into the team is crucial. Finally, they would have to feel positive working in fast-paced learning environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We strongly encourage people of any underrepresented group to apply as we are committed to diversity and work to build an inclusive environment where all people, regardless of gender, race, religion, or background, can thrive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits and other perks of working with us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive salary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employment stock ownership plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;End-year performance-based bonus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;25 days of holidays on a full-time basis&lt;/li&gt

&lt;p&gt;QphoX is looking for a new member to join us in developing and building our quantum transducers. We are looking to expand our team with a &lt;strong&gt;Nanofabrication Production Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;. As a member of our team, you will help develop and produce the next generation of integrated quantum devices and take their performance to the next level. You will be trained to become part of one of the world’s leading groups in developing microwave to optical transducers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be involved in:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fabrication of transducer devices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing and improving processes in cleanroom to ensure their quality covering operation, calibration, and optimization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with other teams to ensure processes align with specifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing solutions to prevent recurring issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Following&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;the transition of new process technologies from R&amp;amp;D to scaling and production&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining accurate documentation of processes, procedures, and specifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinating scheduled preventive maintenance for equipment, and develop validation requirements for special processes, providing assistance in executing qualification protocols&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implementing enhancements to processes to improve key performance metrics such as yield, throughput, and cycle time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working in a diverse and multi-disciplinary team of employees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are suitable for this role if you have &lt;strong&gt;one or several&lt;/strong&gt; of the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in semiconductor or TFLN industry fabrication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in cutting-edge nano/micro-fabrication techniques, ensuring precision and reliability in every process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience using statistics to analyze test results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Embrace collaboration and foster a supportive team environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Value diverse perspectives and open communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organized and adaptable, with an interest for problem-solving to overcome challenges&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;No prior experience in or knowledge of quantum physics is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Supplementary skills set:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with TFLN industry processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintenance of nanofabrication tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with quality management or quality control&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supplier management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Ideal Candidate:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our ideal candidate would be self-motivated with a meticulous attention to detail, ensuring transparency and informed decision-making within our organization. They would actively contribute to enhancing standard protocols for our transducers fabrication through thorough analysis and collaborative efforts with cross-functional teams, aiming for maximizing efficiency, quality, and industrial scalability. Additionally, our ideal candidate would foster a supportive and collaborative work environment where every team member&#39;s voice is valued and respected.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Background and Education level required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Material sciences, or nanoscience, or chemistry, or applied sciences, or physics, or quality control&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relevant experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BSc, MSc, or PhD&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
