&lt;li&gt;Building, testing, troubleshooting, and improving electro-optical assemblies and subsystems according to procedures and quality standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting prototype builds, pilot production, and new product introduction activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performing functional testing, diagnostics, and failure analysis of assemblies and devices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with cross-functional engineering teams to optimize product designs, assembly processes, and manufacturing workflows, improving production efficiency, quality, and yield.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creating and maintaining assembly documentation, work instructions, and production records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitoring inventory levels and coordinating material requirements to support production schedules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working in a diverse and multidisciplinary team of engineers and scientists.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
